An Academic Warning is issued by the Office of Undergraduate Advising if a student fails to meet one or more of the following standards: 
1. A single or more grade of F or NC (excluding PE courses) in a term; 
2. A second or more grade of D (D, D -, D+) over the student’s tenure at DKU; 
3. Failure to meet the term credit requirements; 
4. A grade of C - or below for CAPSTONE 495 Signature Work Capstone I; 
5. Failure to meet Signature Work milestones and submission deadlines.
